  "texts": [
    "The QLoRA method (Hu et al., 2021) explains why our top model has a rank of 16 instead of 128, contrary to common expectations (more details reagrding QLoRA hyperparameters in App.",
    "Drawing from the widespread presence of low-rank structures, as highlighted by prior studies (Li et al., 2016 (Li et al.,, 2019;; Grasedyck et al., 2013), we leverage the intrinsic low-rank structure in our problem, as emphasized in Hu et al. (2021).",
    "It is well-established that many tasks, particularly involving heavily overparametrized models, exhibit low-rank properties post-training (Oymak et al., 2019).",
    "Overall, our systems demonstrate remarkably high overall accuracy, being less than 10% lower than human performance and more than 30% greater than ChatGPT.",
    "This suggests our methods' proficiency in understanding and detecting wordplay patterns, consistently addressing ambiguity irrespective of contextual and semantic variations in brain teasers."
  ]
